webpackJsonp([24514147235673],{536:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{frontmatter:{title:"Escape button in Macbook Pro without using toucbar",date:"2018-01-11T22:00:00.000Z",tags:["Macbook","MacOS","Productivity","Keyboard"]},timeToRead:3,html:'<p>The fact that you have opened this article means that you are already aware of one the biggest problems of Macbook Pro 2016+ models - the <a href="https://developer.apple.com/macos/touch-bar/">touchbar</a>.</p>\n<p>The touchbar is something Apple have decided to enforce on users as part of their keyboards. It\'s not a problem per-se for most users and certainly the bar can serve as a good tool if used properly. The bar becomes a problem for developers, system administrators and all other power users who need a physical key for the <code class="language-text">Esc</code> (escape).</p>\n<p>I personally understand Apple to an extend - how do you force someone to use the touchbar? You force him to NEED to do something with it, otherwise he will continue with old habits.</p>\n<p>I mean, let\'s be honest, the trackpad in 2016+ models is HUGE. Realistically, it could be a bit tighter to let the Fn keys and its row just be there with no problems!</p>\n<p>And back to the question of adding an <code class="language-text">Esc</code> key on a physical place you expect and want it to be?</p>\n<h2 id="how-to-add-code-classlanguage-textesccode---3-possible-ways"><a href="#how-to-add-code-classlanguage-textesccode---3-possible-ways" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>How to add <code class="language-text">Esc</code> - 3 possible ways</h2>\n<h3 id="solution-1-change-modifier-keys"><a href="#solution-1-change-modifier-keys" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Solution 1: Change modifier keys</h3>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/macos-escape-conventional-4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410-04494.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 89.98609179415855%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Adding escape key in MacOS by conventional means"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/macos-escape-conventional-4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410-6f08c.png"\n        srcset="/static/macos-escape-conventional-4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410-c1ddb.png 180w,\n/static/macos-escape-conventional-4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410-aa93f.png 360w,\n/static/macos-escape-conventional-4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410-6f08c.png 720w,\n/static/macos-escape-conventional-4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410-78b35.png 1080w,\n/static/macos-escape-conventional-4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410-04494.png 1438w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>It\'s the <a href="https://support.apple.com/kb/PH25240?locale=en_IE">official solution</a> which you\'ll find first on Google. No problems with it as long as you\'re ok to let go of the <code class="language-text">Caps Lock</code>. Who needs it anyway, they said?</p>\n<h3 id="solution-2-find-software-to-map-keys"><a href="#solution-2-find-software-to-map-keys" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Solution 2: Find software to map keys</h3>\n<p>Natural reflex to find an app which extends on an existing system API. Appears that at some point of time, quite <a href="https://developer.apple.com/library/content/technotes/tn2450/_index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/DTS40017618-CH1-KEY_TABLE_USAGES">important changes</a> happened and that\'s why you\'ll see controversial opinions on <a href="https://pqrs.org/osx/karabiner/">Karabiner</a> "before and after".</p>\n<p>So, apart from the app under question, you can go advanced with <a href="https://www.boastr.net/">BetterTouchTool</a> and similar premium solutions.</p>\n<p>In short, there are apps on the market - you can spend time searching and trying and evaluating how much it worths spending money on mapping a key or two if that is your goal ...</p>\n<h3 id="solution-3-go-low-level"><a href="#solution-3-go-low-level" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Solution 3: Go low-level</h3>\n<p>There\'s <a href="http://www.manpagez.com/man/1/hidutil/">hidutil</a> and the IOKit HID APIs. Probably there are more, these are the initial options I came upon reading the technical note mentioned earlier. You get the idea here - you do it lightly and your way on the experimentation path.</p>\n<h2 id="what-worked-for-me"><a href="#what-worked-for-me" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>What worked for me</h2>\n<p>To save you time, I\'m giving you this right away: <a href="https://pqrs.org/osx/karabiner/">Karabiner</a>.</p>\n<p>Basically, my scenario was trickier than standard keyboards because on the left of 1 I have the key for new paragraph (ISO) and not the tilde (ANSI). The discussion in <a href="https://github.com/tekezo/Karabiner-Elements/issues/931">this issue</a> could already be a hint for you what we\'re going to do.</p>\n<p>Select to the right layout of keyboard:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/macos-escape-set-keyboard-7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081-b03b7.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 63.09639727361246%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Setting up the keyboard"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/macos-escape-set-keyboard-7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081-6f08c.png"\n        srcset="/static/macos-escape-set-keyboard-7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081-c1ddb.png 180w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-keyboard-7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081-aa93f.png 360w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-keyboard-7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081-6f08c.png 720w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-keyboard-7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081-78b35.png 1080w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-keyboard-7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081-b741e.png 1440w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-keyboard-7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081-b03b7.png 2054w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In my case, I had to select <code class="language-text">ANSI</code> instead of <code class="language-text">ISO</code>, even though the actual hardware keyboard is <code class="language-text">ISO</code>. If you are honest here, as soon as you map the <code class="language-text">Esc</code> on the <code class="language-text">non_us_backslack</code>, your new paragraph key will go on the tilde ... Not cool. Just as in the issue on github.</p>\n<p>Then, just do the mapping as you would do if you didn\'t know about any of the possible edge cases described above ;)</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/macos-escape-set-mapping-fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815-6b229.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 63.9423076923077%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Setting up the mapping for escape key in MacOS"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/macos-escape-set-mapping-fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815-6f08c.png"\n        srcset="/static/macos-escape-set-mapping-fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815-c1ddb.png 180w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-mapping-fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815-aa93f.png 360w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-mapping-fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815-6f08c.png 720w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-mapping-fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815-78b35.png 1080w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-mapping-fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815-b741e.png 1440w,\n/static/macos-escape-set-mapping-fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815-6b229.png 2080w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>And that\'s it! Now that physical key next to the fancy touchbar will be your <code class="language-text">Esc</code> as normal :)</p>'}},pathContext:{slug:"escaping-macbook-pro-touchbar"}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---escaping-macbook-pro-touchbar-470965e0a208d6e94766.js.map